Improve Intent Matching Quality with Bot Training

Help your bot improve its conversation quality with Bot Training. Bot Training shows you the intent that the bot identified from an utterance. Then you can tell your bot if it was right, or you can correct the bot if it was wrong.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Einstein Bots is available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Setup for Einstein Bots is available in Lightning Experience.
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To build and manage Einstein Bots:	
Customize Application

OR

Modify Metadata

OR

Manage Bots


To manage intent sets and bot training:	
Customize Application

OR

Modify Metadata

OR

Manage Bots

OR

Manage Bot Training Data

Help your bot improve its conversation quality with Bot Training. 

Bot Training shows you the intent that the bot identified from an utterance. You can tell your bot if it was right, or correct the bot if it was wrong.

To access Bot Training: 
Make sure to select a language for the bot and make sure Store Einstein Bots conversation data is selected.
Enter the Model Management page, then click Build Model.
After the build is completed, activate and interact with your bot to collect text for bot training. 
New customer inputs don’t appear in Bot Training in real time and can take up to 24 hours to populate.

To train a bot: 
Click Train Bot from the Model Management page.
The Bot Training menu shows customer inputs and the bot’s top intent prediction. Use buttons to confirm the intent, ignore the utterance, or reclassify to another intent.

You can also reclassify utterances to Einstein-enabled dialog intents or exact matching intents.
Use Bulk Action buttons from the list view to act on many inputs at once.
After working through all open training items, click Build Model to integrate your suggestions.
title: Improving Intent Matching Quality with Bot Training
